y%20anticipated%20the%20start%20of%20school%20each%20fall%20and%20their%20relief%20as%20it%20ended%20nine%20months%20later.%20I%20loved%20their%20enthusiasm%20for%20learning%2C%20especially%20during%20their%20earliest%20years%20in%20a%20classroom.%20They%20took%20their%20jobs%20as%20students%20seriously%20but%20were%20always%20eager%20to%20celebrate%20that%20final%20assignment%20and%2010%20weeks%20off%20before%20starting%20the%20cycle%20over%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20a%20different%20response.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20me%2C%20watching%20the%20months%20tick%20by%20brought%20on%20waves%20of%20melancholy.%20It%20made%20me%20sad%20to%20realize%20how%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-i-slowed-down-time-to-enjoy-my-kids-more-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equickly%20the%20years%20were%20passing%3C%2Fa%3E.%20On%20top%20of%20that%2C%20as%20a%20single%20mother%2C%20it%20was%20up%20to%20me%20to%20find%20ways%20to%20keep%20them%20safe%20and%20occupied%20during%20the%20weeks%20the%20school%20doors%20were%20locked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e92b2285-8d9a-48a0-b3b1-76eeb59eb144%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20flexible%20work%20schedule%20allowed%20me%20to%20be%20with%20my%20kids%20in%20the%20summer%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20fortunate%20to%20have%20a%20flexible%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwfh-bigger-driver-entry-level-job-woes-ai-researchers-say-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ework-from-home%20schedule%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20could%20accommodate%20all%20their%20activities.%20It%20worked%20well%20during%20the%20three%20seasons%20they%20were%20at%20school.%20It%20was%20more%20challenging%20during%20the%20summer.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Boy%20tanning%20at%20beach%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3c2c1e360acd489560a828%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20felt%20guilty%20for%20working%20through%20the%20summer%20months.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20that%20I%20didn't%20welcome%20the%20slower%20pace%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworld-hottest-year-ever-history-climate-crisis-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewarmer%20months%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20we%20swapped%20the%20frenzy%20of%20early-morning%20wake-ups%20for%20a%20calmer%2C%20more%20relaxed%20entry%20into%20a%20less%20structured%20day.%20It%20was%20the%20tension%20I%20felt%20while%20sequestered%20in%20my%20home%20office%2C%20wondering%20what%20they%20might%20be%20doing%20and%20feeling%20guilty%20for%20not%20offering%20them%20an%20enhanced%20experience%20while%20they%20were%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20promise%20of%20afternoons%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpool-entertaining-cost-save-money-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecommunity%20pool%3C%2Fa%3E%20if%20they%20allowed%20me%20to%20work%20uninterrupted%20in%20the%20mornings%2C%20we%20created%20a%20system%20that%20served%20us%20all%20well%20until%20I%20transitioned%20to%20a%20full-time%2C%20office-based%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e02ef538-dda7-4844-9aac-a52eb8adeb8f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20did%20not%20want%20my%20kids%20to%20be%20home%20alone%20while%20I%20was%20at%20work%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20two%20oldest%20sons%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteen-couldnt-find-summer-job-got-hired-in-another-state-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esummer%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20I%20started%20a%20new%20job%2C%20but%20the%20three%20younger%20kids%20didn't.%20Our%20very%20small%20town%2C%20only%203%20square%20miles%20in%20size%2C%20offered%20daily%20activities%20in%20the%20park%20for%20school-aged%20children%20up%20to%20age%2012.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBelieving%20in%20safety%20in%20numbers%2C%20I%20allowed%20my%20younger%20children%20to%20walk%20to%20the%20park%20together%20to%20participate.%20That%20worked%20for%20a%20few%20years%2C%20but%20given%20the%20spread%20in%20ages%20%E2%80%94%20my%20oldest%20and%20my%20youngest%20share%20the%20same%20birthday%2C%2016%20years%20apart%20%E2%80%94%20they%20quickly%20aged%20out%20of%20the%20program%2C%20and%20I%20had%20to%20find%20alternatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Girl%20doing%20archery%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3c2c4aa25092c74cc9e6b1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22512%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20didn't%20want%20to%20leave%20her%20kids%20alone%20at%20home%20during%20the%20summer.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20daughter%20entered%20her%20teens%2C%20she%20decided%20to%20adopt%20a%20family%20with%20an%20actively%20involved%20father.%20She%20missed%20having%20a%20dad%20in%20her%20life%2C%20so%20she%20latched%20onto%20a%20classmate%20and%20was%20welcomed%20as%20a%20part-time%20member%20of%20their%20household.%20She%20frequently%20slept%20at%20their%20home%2C%20attended%20events%20with%20their%20extended%20family%2C%20and%20even%20went%20camping%20with%20them.%20Occasionally%2C%20my%20youngest%20son%20would%20join%20them%2C%20but%20he%20did%20not%20feel%20as%20attached%20as%20she%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d7b8b1d0-85fb-44ca-be4a-6edb0b660eb7%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20let%20my%20youngest%20son%20travel%20out-of-state%20during%20the%20summer%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20my%20youngest%20was%20a%20preteen%2C%20his%20older%20siblings%20had%20moved%20from%20our%20home.%20They%20were%20forging%20lives%20as%20young%20adults%2C%20making%20him%20an%20only%20child%20in%20a%20large%20family.%20That's%20when%20I%20started%20sending%20him%20on%20vacation%20with%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20two%20consecutive%20summers%2C%20I%20sent%20him%20to%20Michigan%20with%20his%20best%20friend's%20family.%20I%20felt%20relieved%20that%20he%20wasn't%20sitting%20home%20alone%20while%20I%20was%20at%20work.%20He%20enjoyed%20these%20trips%20to%20a%20lakefront%20house%20where%20he%20could%20fish%2C%20pick%20berries%2C%20and%20just%20hang%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20turned%2012%2C%20I%20started%20sending%20him%20to%20San%20Francisco%20each%20summer%20to%20celebrate%20the%20July%20birthday%20he%20shared%20with%20his%20oldest%20brother.%20He%20would%20fly%20across%20the%20country%20on%20his%20own%20to%20spend%20a%20month%20in%20the%20Bay%20Area.%20He%20turned%2016%20in%20a%20college%20dorm%20there%20while%20attending%20a%20summer%20semester%20at%20the%20university%20where%20he%20eventually%20enrolled%20after%20high%20school.%20After%20class%2C%20he'd%20walk%20to%20his%20brother's%20apartment%2C%20where%20they'd%20share%20dinner%20before%20returning%20to%20his%20room%20on%20campus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20lonely%20during%20the%20summer%2C%20but%20I%20think%20it%20was%20a%20good%20decision%20to%20let%20them%20go.%20Even%20though%20I%20missed%20them%2C%20I%20knew%20they%20were%20having%20fun%20with%20people%20who%20cared%20about%20them.%20It%20was%20the%20solution%20that%20resolved%20our%20problem%2C%20but%20also%20enveloped%20them%20in%20the%20love%20of%20more%20people%20who%20cared%20about%20their%20well-being.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-mom-five-kids-summer-break-2026-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1783537501000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3c2ac2360acd489560a81a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-mom-five-kids-summer-break-2026-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20a%20single%20mother%2C%20I%20spent%20years%20finding%20creative%20ways%20to%20keep%20my%20children%20safe%2C%20busy%2C%20and%20connected%