%20an%20attack.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4e6bbbd3b3e457651968d9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENATO's%20new%20strategy%20relies%20on%20uncrewed%20vehicles%2C%20like%20this%20Hunter%20Wolf%20unmanned%20ground%20vehicle%2C%20as%20a%20first%20response%20to%20an%20attack.%3Cp%3ESpc.%20Mariam%20Diallo%2FUS%20Army%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ENew%20documents%20reveal%20NATO%20is%20building%20a%20vast%20AI%20network%20to%20deter%20Russian%20aggression.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20is%20part%20of%20a%20larger%20shift%20that%20foresees%20uncrewed%20systems%20as%20the%20first%20response%20to%20an%20attack.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20strategy%20%26quot%3Bdoes%20not%20replace%20tanks%2C%20artillery%2C%20fighter%20aircraft%2C%20or%20soldiers%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20official%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAlong%20NATO's%20eastern%20flank%2C%20the%20military%20alliance%20is%20no%20longer%20relying%20solely%20on%20tanks%2C%20fighter%20jets%2C%20and%20troops.%20Instead%2C%20it%20is%20building%20a%20vast%20digital%20battlespace%20network%20made%20up%20of%20thousands%20of%20sensors%2C%20drones%2C%20satellites%2C%20and%20artificial%20intelligence.%20The%20goal%3A%20to%20detect%20an%20attack%20on%20allied%20nations%20as%20early%20as%20possible%20and%20block%20the%20attacker%20before%20they%20can%20penetrate%20deeper%20into%20Alliance%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20concept%20is%20called%20the%20Eastern%20Flank%20Deterrence%20Initiative%20(EFDI).%20In%20documents%20obtained%20by%20BILD%20%E2%80%94%20which%2C%20like%20Business%20Insider%2C%20is%20part%20of%20the%20Axel%20Springer%20Global%20Reporters%20Network%20%E2%80%94%20one%20potential%20adversary%20is%20explicitly%20identified%3A%20Russia.%20It%20is%20intended%20not%20only%20to%20offset%20Russia's%20advantage%20in%20mass%20and%20momentum%20%E2%80%94%20large%20troop%20numbers%20and%20rapid%20advances%20%E2%80%94%20but%20also%20to%20discourage%20Moscow%20from%20launching%20an%20attack%20in%20the%20first%20place.%20NATO%20refers%20to%20this%20principle%20as%20%26quot%3Bdeterrence%20by%20denial.%26quot%3B%20It%20is%20expected%20to%20rely%20on%20systems%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpalantir-guide-stopping-world-war-iii-karp-book-review-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPalantir%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20other%20leading%20Western%20defense%20contractors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20strategy%20creates%20a%20vast%20AI-guided%20network%20to%20detect%20and%20strike%20targets%20%E2%80%94%20not%20unlike%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-kill-chain-faster-more-precise-nato-ready-artillery-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epowerful%20web%20Russia%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20built%20fighting%20Ukraine.%20But%20it%20is%20just%20the%20beginning%20of%20a%20much%20larger%20shift%2C%20where%20uncrewed%20systems%20like%20attack%20drones%20and%20remote-controlled%20machine%20gun%20turrets%20will%20be%20NATO's%20first%20line%20of%20defense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221fd39d4c-ec88-45e5-a83f-b55e942c9da7%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20Iron%20Curtain%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20Finland's%20accession%20to%20NATO%20in%202023%2C%20the%20Alliance's%20shared%20border%20with%20Russia%20expanded%20significantly.%20Today%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnato-eastern-flank-prepares-to-fend-off-russia-without-us-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENATO's%20eastern%20border%3C%2Fa%3E%20stretches%20from%20Finland%20through%20Estonia%2C%20Latvia%2C%20Lithuania%2C%20and%20Poland%20to%20Romania%20on%20the%20Black%20Sea.%20It%20also%20includes%20the%20border%20with%20Belarus%2C%20Russia's%20close%20ally.%20Along%20this%20entire%20line%2C%20EFDI%20is%20intended%20to%20strengthen%20the%20Alliance's%20defense%20through%20a%20system%20of%20sensors%2C%20drones%2C%20command%20networks%2C%20and%20conventional%20military%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22NATO's%20border%20with%20Russia%20and%20Belarus%20runs%20for%20nearly%202%2C600%20kilometers.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a4e6b5fd3a449ec3445f44a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221892%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBild%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20decades%2C%20NATO%20relied%20on%20the%20principle%20of%20%26quot%3Bdeterrence%20by%20punishment.%26quot%3B%20The%20idea%20was%20that%20if%20Russia%20attacked%20NATO%20territory%2C%20tanks%2C%20artillery%2C%20fighter%20aircraft%2C%20and%20ground%20troops%20would%20repel%20the%20assault%20and%20later%20recapture%20lost%20territory.%20These%20conventional%20capabilities%20will%20remain%20the%20backbone%20of%20NATO's%20defense.%20Leopard%202%20tanks%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fabrams-tank-built-fight-soviets-apparently-at-war-russian-soil-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EM1%20Abrams%20tanks%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20HIMARS%20rocket%20launchers%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-army-recognizes-artillery-problem-needs-to-find-fix-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eartillery%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20F-35%20fighter%20jets%20will%20continue%20to%20play%20an%20essential%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20new%2C%20however%2C%20is%20an%20additional%20layer%20of%20defense.%20Its%20purpose%20is%20to%20detect%2C%20delay%2C%20and%20engage%20an%20adversary%20before%20NATO's%20conventional%20ground%20forces%20come%20into%20contact%20with%20it%2C%20allowing%20those%20forces%20to%20preserve%20their%20combat%20power%20and%20be%20committed%20only%20at%20the%20decisive%20moment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEFDI%20does%20not%20replace%20tanks%2C%20artillery%2C%20fighter%20aircraft%2C%20or%20soldiers%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Maj.%20Matt%20Blubaugh%2C%20a%20spokesman%20for%20US%20Army%20Europe%20and%20Africa.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20designed%20to%20help%20preserve%20their%20combat%2